Local media report that she became depressed when she broached the subject of marriage and he laughed at her, saying their relationship was not serious.

She had said previously that he had 'harassed' her for the numbers of her schoolfriends, The Times of India reported.

The girl, who has not been named, kept the relationship hidden from her family

Her family, from Bangalore, told police they had no idea about the relationship and only discovered it when her mother found her dead inside their locked house.

The schoolgirl had taken her younger brother to a cousin's house before hanging herself.

She started dating the man - a second year student at Seshadripuram College, in Yelahanka - after be befriended her on the social network site.

There was no internet at her home so she travelled to cafes in order to speak to him online.

Police say he invited her to his house where they had sex.

